The paper deals with structural and model theoretic properties of classes of graphs with bounded linear rankwidth, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the relationship between linear rankwidth and other graph parameters such as cliquewidth and pathwidth, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses tools from logic and model theory to study these graph classes, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the chromatic number and cographs, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the perspective of studying classes with low linear rankwidth covers, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
